<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7579> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7579" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Aed. desig. 42? He was killed by the soldiers who had killed his father (see below, no. 7), perhaps while only aedile designate since there appears to have been little time for entrance upon office (App. BC 4.18; see MRR 2.359). (TJC)\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6149> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6149" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Son of an ex-Praetor who was rewarded for betraying his father by election to the aedileship, presumably for 42, but was killed while in office by soldiers (App. BC 4.18; cf. Val. Max. 9.11.6). See 58, Praetors; Lübker no. 3." .
